Learn to use grouping constructs in .NET. Grouping constructs delineate subexpressions of a regular expression and capture substrings of an input string.

You can mark an optional reference to a class as unowned. In terms of the ARC ownership model, an unowned optional reference and a weak reference can both be used in the same contexts. The difference is that when you use an unowned optional reference, you‚Äôre responsible for making sure it always refers to a valid object or is set to nil.
